column37: FUNCTION: Adapter protein for the cul3 E3 ubiquitin-protein ligase complex (By similarity). Involved in late neuronal development and muscle formation (PubMed:18855900). {ECO:0000250|UniProtKB:A9JRD8, ECO:0000269|PubMed:18855900}.
column54: SUBUNIT: Homodimer and heterodimer. Interacts with cul3 via the BTB domain. {ECO:0000269|PubMed:18855900}.
column56: DEVELOPMENTAL STAGE: Highly expressed in the developing nervous system. {ECO:0000269|PubMed:18855900}.
column66: DISRUPTION PHENOTYPE: Embryos show strong defects in late neuronal markers and strongly reduced and disorganized axons while early neural development is unaffected. Muscle development is also affected. {ECO:0000269|PubMed:18855900}.
column70: SUBCELLULAR LOCATION: Cytoplasm {ECO:0000269|PubMed:18855900}. Note=Found in punctated bodies in the cytoplasm. {ECO:0000269|PubMed:18855900}.
